Articles.Content:
Hello

@timmers_uk and I have arranged that I will update the Spacedock.info listing with the latest release from my Github Keepfit fork.

Could someone (looking at @Kerbas_ad_astra) try out the Github release before I update the Spacedock listing. Also if you could run the download through an anti-virus scanner for good measure.

Recompiled version uploaded to Spacedock.

Whenever I go to the map view and back in flight, the KeepFit window will open. It wasn't supposed to be like that, but I can't seem to figure out which part of the code to look at; if you have a keen sense about these things, please leave a hint for me.

Edit:

I have removed a feature and recompiled. Version 0.12.3.4 should no longer open the KeepFit window every time you go back from map view.

Edited October 11, 2017 by Rodhern
mini-update to ver. 0.12.3.4.

On 10/6/2017 at 12:37 PM, Rodhern said:

Recompiled version uploaded to Spacedock.

Whenever I go to the map view and back in flight, the KeepFit window will open. It wasn't supposed to be like that, but I can't seem to figure out which part of the code to look at; if you have a keen sense about these things, please leave a hint for me.

Edit:

I have removed a feature and recompiled. Version 0.12.3.4 should no longer open the KeepFit window every time you go back from map view.

Not sure if you could, perhaps, take a look at this issue: https://github.com/timmersuk/Timmers_KSP/issues/10

Minor one... But still.

On 10/20/2017 at 5:10 AM, Galenmacil said:

Not sure if you could, perhaps, take a look at this issue: https://github.com/timmersuk/Timmers_KSP/issues/10

Minor one... But still.

I have changed the 'aqua' string to its Unity equivalent '#00ffffff'. I didn't check to see if there is a problem for (lime coloured) 'Exercising' too. Let me know if there is, then I will make another mini-update. The update is just uploaded to Spacedock.

What a cool mod!  Two questions:

1. Does thia work with deep freeze?  Thawing kerbals suspend their need for exercise?

2. Instead of the porkworks parts pack,  is it all the same if I use the habitats from linnuxgurugamer's tokamak pack,  which contais the same parts,  only refurbished?
Couldn't find anything else in the thread about this - does this mod have any gameplay compatibility issues with Kerbal Health?

Feel free  to take what I say with a grain of salt, but I'm pretty OCD about those things and from all I've been able to tell, it has no issues with Kerbal Health, if anything, they seem to synergize.

 

I'm using Health, Fit , Tac LS and Dangit(entropy) together as we speak and all is well.  Getting USI's MKS is a good idea to support the both of them.

Edited November 28, 2017 by Fergrim

@Rocketryleigh @Rodhern

Well *blush* looks like I was some kind of wrong.  I updated to the latest version and I don't even see the mod popping up at all.

 

Getting zero sign of it in difficulty settings, buttons, from anywhere.  Is this happening to anyone else?  And if so, do you have Kerbal Health?

Does it conflict, perhaps, with deadly reentry?

Edited November 28, 2017 by Fergrim

2 hours ago, Fergrim said:

I updated to the latest version and I don't even see the mod popping up at all.

If you havn't already, maybe you could check or upload the log file. If we are lucky there could be some hints in there.

Edit: You are on KSP 1.3.1 right?

Edited November 28, 2017 by Rodhern

Yes sir, and I'll do that now.

Also what might save us some time:  Should I be seeing Fitness in the difficulty options or as a button prior to actually putting a kerbal in a vessel/in space?

 

 

26 minutes ago, Rodhern said:

If you havn't already, maybe you could check or upload the log file. If we are lucky there could be some hints in there.

Edit: You are on KSP 1.3.1 right?

And here you are

https://www.dropbox.com/preview/KSP.log?role=personal

And to be clear, yes, I'm most definitely in 1.3.1

3 minutes ago, Fergrim said:

Should I be seeing Fitness in the difficulty options or as a button prior to actually putting a kerbal in a vessel/in space?

A button is supposed to be there, to bring up the status window(s).

My install folder seems to be proper, and dang, I think I'm running every mod you have a .cfg for haha

I hope there's something obvious in my logs, I really wanted to use this.

 

It looks to me like it's getting caught up on miniAVC?

Edited November 28, 2017 by Fergrim
I don't have a Dropbox account (I don't think). I cannot read the uploaded log file. Is there an easy-ish fix you can do?

No, i was just sort of talking out of my butt, but i can paste the segment with keepfit and maybe it means something to you.  Sorry about that I forgot about spoiler tags and I do really appreciate the help.

A few months ago, I asked @timmers_uk and @Rodhern (who unfortunately had not logged in for over a year, nor since) for permission to resurrect this mod when CLS was updated for KSP 1.8+.  Timmers granted me permission, and now that @micha has updated CLS, it's time to bring back KeepFit:

It's not just a straight recompiling, though -- I've changed the core logic so that, instead of updating e.g. the long-term G-loading once every three minutes (and always starting from zero, even at launch), the mod now tracks each exposure interval as a rolling average which is initialized to local gravity when a vessel is loaded.
